Each party must satisfy itself as to the effectiveness and appropriateness of this document and ensure it is used and/or adapted to reflect the commercial intentions and legal and regulatory obligations of the parties.  Parties should seek legal, tax and accounting advice and consult with any other adviser they deem appropriate prior to using this document.

ISDA has not undertaken to review any applicable laws and regulations of any jurisdiction in which this document may be used or of any jurisdiction whose laws or regulations affect derivative contracts, indices, securities and/or currencies that may be the subject of a privately negotiated derivative transaction.  Parties are therefore advised to consider the application of any relevant jurisdictionâ€™s legal, regulatory, tax, accounting, exchange or other requirements that may exist in connection with using this document.
